  "summary": {
    "as": "Passed Senate amended",
    "asOf": "2011-07-27",
    "date": "2011-08-10T12:21:32Z",
    "text": "All-American Flag Act - Requires any flags of the United States acquired for use by the federal government to be entirely manufactured in the United States, from articles, materials, or supplies entirely grown, produced, or manufactured in the United States.\u00a0 Allows the head of an executive agency to waive such requirement if its application would cause unreasonable costs or delays or would adversely affect a U.S. company.\n\nRequires the Federal Acquisition Regulatory Council to amend the Federal Acquisition Regulation to implement this Act.\n\nRequires this Act to be applied in a manner consistent with U.S. obligations under international agreements."
  },
